SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1773421880
OL,3,CResidents facing thousands in building
OL,4,Ccosts hope new laws will provide relief
OL,6,FThe Building Safety (Wales) Bill
OL,7,Fcreates a new safety regime covering
OL,8,Fthe management of multi-occupied
OL,9,Fresidential buildings.
OL,11,FThe Bill categorises buildings into
OL,12,Fthree main groups, with stricter
OL,13,Fregulations enforced on buildings
OL,14,Fwhich are taller.
OL,16,FThe fire safety provisions will also
OL,17,Fapply to Houses in Multiple Occupation
OL,18,F(HMOs) which are not let under a
OL,19,Fsingle tenancy.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/15
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1773421880
OL,3,CResidents facing thousands in building
OL,4,Ccosts hope new laws will provide relief
OL,6,FThere are three main principles that
OL,7,Fare designed to guide the
OL,8,Fimplementation of the Bill; safety,
OL,9,Faccountability, and resident voices.
OL,11,FThe legislation will create a
OL,12,Fstatutory duty for landlords or owners
OL,13,Fto repair any damage which could lead
OL,14,Fto the spread of fire. The accountable
OL,15,Fperson (such as landlords and owners)
OL,16,Fwill have to do this as soon as
OL,17,Fpossible.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/15
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1773421880
OL,3,CResidents facing thousands in building
OL,4,Ccosts hope new laws will provide relief
OL,6,FAll multi-occupied residential
OL,7,Fbuildings will need a fire risk
OL,8,Fassessment, which has to be carried
OL,9,Fout by a 'competent person'. Landlords
OL,10,Fare no longer able to do 'self
OL,11,Fassessments' but it is their
OL,12,Fresponsibility to ensure the
OL,13,Fassessment is appropriately completed
OL,14,Fby a professional.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/15
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1773421880
OL,3,CResidents facing thousands in building
OL,4,Ccosts hope new laws will provide relief
OL,6,FFor category 1 and 2 buildings (at
OL,7,Fleast 11 metres tall), a new legal
OL,8,Fduty will be created to ensure the
OL,9,Fstructural safety of buildings. The
OL,10,Faccountable person (e.g. the owner or
OL,11,Flandlord) must ensure a structural
OL,12,Frisk assessment is carried out by
OL,13,Fsomeone with 'sufficient expertise'.
OL,14,FResidents also have a legal duty to
OL,15,Fnot to interfere with elements of the
OL,16,Fbuilding which can put its structural
OL,17,Fintegrity at risk.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/15
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1773421880
OL,3,CResidents facing thousands in building
OL,4,Ccosts hope new laws will provide relief
OL,6,FThe tallest buildings (category 1)
OL,7,Fwill get a more comprehensive
OL,8,Fassessment called a safety case
OL,9,Freport. This report proves all risk
OL,10,Fincluding fire and structural are
OL,11,Fconstantly being managed.
OL,13,FThis section of the Bill defines who
OL,14,Fis responsible for assessing and
OL,15,Fmanaging risks, aimed at providing a
OL,16,Fclear line of accountability.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/15
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1773421880
OL,3,CResidents facing thousands in building
OL,4,Ccosts hope new laws will provide relief
OL,6,FIt will create a legal requirement to
OL,7,Fkeep all assessments in a digital
OL,8,Fformat so they are easily accessible,
OL,9,Fand provides a clear history of the
OL,10,Fbuildings safety.
OL,12,FThree regional building safety
OL,13,Fauthorities will be created across
OL,14,FWales. They will be made up of the 22
OL,15,Flocal authorities, in collaboration
OL,16,Fwith fire and rescue services.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/15
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1773421880
OL,3,CResidents facing thousands in building
OL,4,Ccosts hope new laws will provide relief
OL,6,FCategory 1 and 2 buildings will have
OL,7,Fto register with building authorities.
OL,8,FIt will become a criminal offence for
OL,9,Fpeople to live in these buildings if
OL,10,Fthey are not registered with the
OL,11,Fauthorities.
OL,13,FThe building safety authorities will
OL,14,Falso have the ability to issue fixed
OL,15,Fpenalty notices for administrative
OL,16,Ffailures and pursue criminal
OL,17,Fprosecution for serious safety
OL,18,Fbreaches.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G13/15
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46714
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1773421880
OL,3,CResidents facing thousands in building
OL,4,Ccosts hope new laws will provide relief
OL,6,FThe Bill aims to give residents more
OL,7,Fpower in dealing with fire and safety
OL,8,Fissues.
OL,10,FResidents will be able to apply to the
OL,11,Fresidential property tribunal to force
OL,12,Fa landlord to fix safety defects.
OL,14,FThe Government and residents will have
OL,15,Fthe ability to sue developers or
OL,16,Fparent companies to pay for safety
OL,17,Frepairs, which is designed to protect
OL,18,Fleaseholders from huge costs
OL,19,Fsurrounding issues with things like
OL,20,Fcladding.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G14/15
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,468,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46715
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F467A1773421880
OL,3,CResidents facing thousands in building
OL,4,Ccosts hope new laws will provide relief
OL,6,FTransparency will be enhanced for
OL,7,Fresidents as they will get the legally
OL,8,Fenforceable right to see the full fire
OL,9,Frisk assessment, not just a summary.
OL,11,FFollowing the passing of the Bill, the
OL,12,FCabinet Secretary for Housing and
OL,13,FLocal Government, Jayne Bryant, said:
OL,14,F"Today marks a landmark moment for
OL,15,Fbuilding safety in Wales. This
OL,16,Flegislation delivers a new building
OL,17,Fsafety regime for residents across
OL,18,FWales, regardless of building type,
OL,19,Fheight or tenure ` going further than
OL,20,Fanything that exists elsewhere in the
OL,21,FUK."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G15/15
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
